<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>He gained a massive fanbase with a starring role in HBO's hit series, Lovecraft Country. </p>

<p>And Jonathan Majors is set to take his talents to a new world as he joins the Marvel Cinematic Universe, according to Deadline.</p>

<p>The 31-year-old actor is rumored to portray the super-villain Kang the Conqueror in the third installment of Ant-Man.</p>

<p>Congrats! Jonathan Majors is set to take his talents to a new world as he joins the Marvel Cinematic Universe, according to Deadline; seen in 2019</p>

<p>While the studio has yet to confirm, the site reported that Majors will likely 'be one of the main villains in the next installment in the franchise.'  </p>

<p>Kang was originally born in the 30th century of Earth-6311 as Nathaniel Richards and is known in the MCU for his time-traveling capabilities, which makes the character an easy fit for the Ant-Man genre.</p>

<p>The Ant-Man franchise garnered more than $500million after its first debut in July 2015, with stars Paul Rudd, Michael Douglas and Evangeline Lilly.  </p>

<p>Big time: The 31-year-old actor is rumored to portray the super-villain Kang the Conqueror in the third installment of Ant-Man</p>

<p>A second installment, Ant-Man and The Wasp, was released in 2018 and grossed more than $600million worldwide.</p>

<p>Director Peyton Reed confirmed on SiriusXM’s The Jess Cagle Show in August that production was 'working away' on the upcoming film despite the global pandemic. </p>

<p>'There’s some really really really exciting things in store, none of which of course I could speak to you about right now, as is the Marvel way,' he said.  </p>

<p>Action! Majors took on the role of Atticus Freeman in the HBO breakout show produced by Jordan Peele and J.J. Abrams; seen in 2019</p>

<p>'I think the third movie is going to be a much bigger, more sprawling movie than the first two. It’s going to have a very different visual template.'</p>

<p>After starring in Spike Lee's war drama Da 5 Bloods, Majors took on the role of Atticus Freeman in the HBO breakout show produced by Jordan Peele and J.J. Abrams.</p>

<p>The series was created by Misha Greene and follows Atticus as he travels across the US in the '50s.</p>

